   128	## 3.06.4 Cross-area dependencies
   129	
   130	| Dependency | Where it surfaced in Project Management | Where it's decided |
   131	|---|---|---|
   132	| **Project record framework (financial KPIs)** | D-2 | **BI (§3.09 D-4)** — Project Performance 360 dashboard locked; **Financial Management (§3.08)** — project accounting decided there |
   133	| **IPM and sales-coordinator routing** | D-3 | **Pre-Quote (§3.03 D-8)** — routing model locked; Project Management uses the model |
   134	| **Time tracking (project-GP impact)** | Time tracking against project tasks | **Operations (§3.05 D-7)** — time tracking framework decided |
   135	| **Document storage architecture** | Project documentation, contracts, drawings | **System Setup & Configuration (§3.10 D-3)** |
   136	| **Multi-company / multi-contact relationship model** | Project-level customer / vendor / influencer relationships | **CRM (§3.02 D-4)** — relationship model locked |
   137	| **GP framework (actual vs. commissionable)** | Project profitability reporting | **CRM (§3.02 D-6)** — GP framework locked |
   138	| **Workfront integration (if Path A)** | Bi-directional Workfront ↔ NetSuite Orion sync | **System Setup & Configuration (§3.10 D-6)** — integration architecture |
   139	
   140	## 3.06.5 Recommendation summary
   141	
   142	The merged-company Project Management playbook in shorthand:
   143	
   144	- **Platform architecture:** Path A working default — Workfront retained for project management with NetSuite Orion integration; Path B (Orion native consolidation) feasible if leadership prioritizes platform consolidation
   145	- **Project record:** NetSuite Orion native project record as financial-and-reporting aggregation layer regardless of platform path
   146	- **Role taxonomy:** IPM-and-sales-coordinator routing per Pivot framework; KBM staff role assignments during organizational alignment
   147	- **Resource allocation and capacity management:** Pivot framework adopted; in Workfront under Path A, in Orion native under Path B
   148	- **Project status dashboards:** NetSuite Orion for financial KPIs (Project Performance 360 per BI §3.09 D-4); Workfront for execution status under Path A
   149	- **Time tracking:** Per Operations §3.05 D-7 framework; feeds dual GP and project profitability
   150	
   151	Net read: project management is the most platform-architecture-significant decision in the unification. The recommendation defaults to Workfront retention because Pivot's existing investment is substantial and the PM team is operating proficiently. The alternative (Orion native consolidation) is feasible and may be preferred by leadership for platform-consolidation reasons. Either path leaves NetSuite Orion as the system of record for project financial data.
   152	
   153	## 3.06.6 Decisions for the leadership team
   154	
   155	| # | Decision | Default | Reference |
   156	|---|---|---|---|
   157	| 1a | Project-management platform: Path A (Workfront retained) or Path B (Orion native consolidation) | Path A working default; confirm at session | D-1 |
   158	| 1b | If Path A: bi-directional Workfront ↔ NetSuite Orion integration | Yes | D-1 |
   159	| 2 | NetSuite Orion native project record as merged-company financial-and-reporting aggregation layer | Yes | D-2 |
   160	| 3 | IPM-and-sales-coordinator role taxonomy for the merged-company project team | Yes | D-3 |
   161	| 4 | Pivot's resource allocation and capacity management framework adopted | Yes | D-4 |
   162	| 5 | NetSuite Orion as system of record for project financial KPIs | Yes | D-5 |
   163	
   164	> 6 decisions: 5 with default-yes recommendations and 1 (decision 1a, platform architecture) requiring leadership-team selection during the working session. This is the highest-stakes decision in this section.
