   169	# <a id="_Toc215670897"></a>3 Project Management & Workfront
   170	
   171	## <a id="_Toc215670898"></a>3\.01 Labor Quote Management
   172	
   173	3\.01\.01 Your Business Requirements
   174	
   175	- REQ\-3\.01\.01: Manage 5,300\+ annual labor quote requests from initiation through sales order integration
   176		- Support Designer/Sales initiation → PM review → Estimator → PM finalization → Sales workflow
   177	- __REQ\-3\.01\.02: __Eliminate manual data re\-entry between Workfront, IQ, and D365 systems
   178	- __REQ\-3\.01\.03: __Support automatic routing of labor quote requests to appropriate estimators \(internal or external vendors\)
   179	- __REQ\-3\.01\.04: __Enable partial acceptance of multiple labor quote options \(accept Option 1, reject Option 2\)
   180	- __REQ\-3\.01\.05: __Configure client\-specific quote formatting templates \(80% single line, 20% custom breakdowns\)
   181	- __REQ\-3\.01\.06: __Automatically transfer accepted labor quotes to sales order lines \(replace CAP spec upload\)
   182	- __REQ\-3\.01\.07: __Support USD standard with CAD quote notation capability
   183	
   184	3\.01\.02 Current State Process
   185	
   186	Labor quoting is fragmented across three disconnected systems with manual data transfer at each handoff:
   187	
   188	- Designer/Sales initiates a request in Workfront with scope documents and floor plans
   189	- Admin on the Service Operations Team\. Design / Sales submits request, PM modifies and sends to the estimator in Workfront\. Then admin transfers to IQ\. Estimator completes quote in IQ, and then PM copies info back into Workfront\. \(no integration\)
   190	- Estimator completes quote in IQ; PM manually copies results back to Workfront
   191	- Sales Coordinator manually enters labor line into D365 via CAP spec upload
   192	- Client formatting preferences \(80/20 split\) managed through tribal knowledge
   193	- Multi\-option quotes require manual coordination with no systematic acceptance workflow
   194	
   195	3\.01\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
   196	
   197	Request Engine provides integrated labor quote management, eliminating manual transfers:
   198	
   199	- Designers/Sales initiate requests with attached documents directly in the system
   200	- Automatic routing to estimators based on configurable business rules with audit trail
   201	- Labor Quote Acceptance feature enables selection of specific options or combined quotes
   202	- PDF Composer provides client\-default templates with custom override capability
   203	- Accepted quotes auto\-populate sales order lines with proper GL posting via vendor cross\-reference
   204	
   205	3\.01\.04 Future State Process
   206	
   207	- Designer/Sales initiates labor quote request in Orion Request Engine with integrated document attachment\. In the case of generating multiple quotes \(ST vs OT\) Status for not selected quotes is “cancelled’ but the hidden setting can be configured and also inactivate the record is an option\. Custom status can also be added for the different type request types
   208	- System automatically routes to the assigned Project Manager based on project assignment rules
   209	- PM reviews and enhances the request directly in the system, the system routes to the estimator automatically\. Emails can be sent to an Orion sub vendor, but you will have to select the quoter\. Select a vendor contact and the email can be review and send\. This is included in scope
