_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:105:Pivot Interiors requires a unified platform to replace their current fragmented system landscape consisting of Adobe Workfront, D365, Power BI, and FluidPay for managing pre\-quote activities\. The company processes complex design and labor quote requests across multiple market segments \(Enterprise, Venture, Public Health Care, Government\) with sophisticated workflows that currently require extensive manual coordination between systems\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:163:Pivot currently manages all pre\-quote requests through Adobe Workfront's "Issues" system, which serves as their comprehensive request management platform\. The system supports extensive request types including general requests, design double checks, labor quote requests \(both simple and complex\), customer approval workflows, bill backs, and various proposal types \(standard, GSA\-specific, leasing, third\-party billing, storage agreements\)\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:165:Salespeople initiate project requests through Workfront questionnaire systems that automatically assign project types based on answers, creating sophisticated workflows with conditional logic\. Request routing occurs through automated logic where IPMs receive complex projects while sales reps handle transactional work directly\. The system includes specialized workflows for demo requests requiring delivery coordination and quote bypass processes for specific order types \(WIX, ServiceNet, Delivery Upon Receipt \(DUR\), Quick Quotes, warranty claims\)\. This will be included in the requirement list\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:167:Key pain points include manual data transfer between Workfront, IQ Coordinator, and D365 for financial processing, heavy dependence on individual expertise \(particularly Sherri Nuzum's Workfront knowledge\), and the complexity of managing 20\+ request types that may include redundant variations creating training challenges for new team members\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:173:The platform's request engine configuration enables complex business rules through standard administration tools, supporting everything from simple general requests to sophisticated multi\-stage approval processes\. Request template and field management capabilities provide dynamic form behavior where fields appear based on previous responses, replicating Pivot's current Workfront questionnaire logic\. The solution's request routing functionality automatically assigns requests based on configurable criteria including customer segment, project complexity, and team member specialization\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:183:Request routing will allow for assigning of  PMs to complex projects based on salesperson alignment while directing transactional requests to sales coordinators\. Demo requests allows the  collection, delivery, and contact information while triggering fulfillment workflows, and specialized requests\.  Orion provides labor quote functionality for internal and external \(union\) labor\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:481:The current process lacks standardization for requirements collection and often relies on informal communication between team members\. Job site analysis information may be captured in Workfront projects, email communications, or estimator notes, creating inconsistency in data quality and availability for quote accuracy\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:501:Will client badging requirements/vaccinations/etc\. be part of site conditions \(Sandra/Brian/Marie\)
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:503:Will this form be at the customer level or project? Ideally at the client address level, since jobsite conditions are fairly constant by address\. \(Sandra\) \+1 Brian
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:517:Pivot's project initiation currently occurs through Workfront with salespeople creating project requests through questionnaire systems\. Projects are automatically categorized based on responses, with IPMs assigned for complex projects while transactional work routes directly to sales coordinators\. The system provides project\-level visibility across all related orders and maintains umbrella project structure for comprehensive customer management\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:519:Project setup involves manual coordination between Workfront project creation and D365 financial setup, requiring sales coordinators to transfer project information for quote creation and customer financial dimension configuration\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:539:Will we have the opportunity to manually trigger the project creation?  I’m thinking about our legacy clients, who send in purchase orders for us to order\.  We don’t have an opportunity for this as we weren’t expecting it\.  \(Sandra\)
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:543:Will smart numbering of Project/Quote/Sales Order/Purchase Order be implemented? \(Sandra\)
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:559:Pivot tracks design capacity through Workfront time tracking with an 80% utilization target, supported by Power BI reporting that blends data from multiple systems\. Users \(Design Studio Leads\) manage all design assignments based on both capacity availability and project\-specific skill requirements, with assignment decisions occurring at the request level\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:561:Design double\-check processes involve detailed markup logs that track error types and quality metrics, providing valuable reporting data but requiring manual form completion and coordination\. The current system requires manual coordination between Workfront time entries and Power BI reporting for complete visibility into designer utilization and project profitability\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:592:2. Enable team management by Sales Person maintaining current PM \(including IPM\) \-salesperson alignment relationships
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:600:Pivot uses a sophisticated hybrid team assignment approach where Implementation Project Managers \(IPMs\) are aligned to specific salespeople and handle their complex projects, while users manage all design resource assignments regardless of salesperson alignment\. This creates a matrix organization that optimizes both customer relationship continuity and resource utilization\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:602:Project creation triggers IPM assignment based on salesperson alignment and project complexity, with sales coordinators handling simple transactional projects without IPM involvement\. The current system provides project\-level team visibility across the entire lifecycle from request through completion but requires manual coordination to maintain team assignments and resource balancing\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:608:Team management by Sales Person functionality preserves current IPM\-salesperson relationships while providing capacity\-aware assignment recommendations for optimal resource utilization\. Role\-based assignments and responsibilities ensure appropriate skill matching and workload distribution, while influencer and customer contact assignment capabilities support complex project communication coordination\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:614:Team assignments will occur automatically through Order Team Management rules that maintain IPM\-salesperson relationships while enabling user optimization of design resources\. The system will provide cross\-functional visibility into team assignments and project status through integrated dashboards that eliminate manual coordination requirements\.
_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:666:Will a “New Customer Application” form be possible, to send from Orion \(similar to the quote approval process\)?  \(Sandra\)

