Operations/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_Operations_v1.0.md:973:**REQ-016: Configure time tracking to impact project GP (not GL) (ALIGNS)**
Operations/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_Operations_v1.0.md:975:This is an important distinction that not all dealers make. Time entries logged by PMs and designers will impact the gross profit (GP) calculations of projects, allowing KBM Hogue to see true project profitability including resource costs. However, time tracking does NOT impact the general ledger (GL). Payroll is handled separately through a payroll integration (currently Paylocity), which journals payroll costs directly to GL. Time tracking is purely about project costing, not payroll processing.
Operations/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_Operations_v1.0.md:977:**REQ-017: Configure PM flat rate structure (internal cost and external billing) (ALIGNS)**
Operations/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_Operations_v1.0.md:979:PMs are paid/costed on a flat rate basis (not hourly). Each PM has an internal rate (what it costs the company when that PM logs time—used for project costing) and an external rate (what clients are billed for PM time on a SOW). Some clients have negotiated different PM rates under their service agreements.
Operations/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_Operations_v1.0.md:987:Some clients have negotiated specific PM or design rates in their service agreements. These client-specific rates override standard rates when the client is selected. However, the internal cost (what impacts project GP) remains standard—only the revenue side (what client is billed) changes for negotiated arrangements.
